title: 12-Year-Old Sydney Shark Attack Victim Nico Antic Honoured With Bondi Paddle-Out | 10 News
description: Hundreds of people banded together today in Bondi for a paddle-out to pay tribute to shark attack victim Nico Antic. title: 5YO Liam Conejo Ramos And Dad Released From ICE Detention | 10 News
description: Five-year-old Liam Conejo Ramos and his father, who were detained by ICE agents in Minnesota an held at a detention facility in Texas, have been released and returned home following a judge's order.  Neighbours and school officials say that on January 20, federal immigration officers use the five-year-old as "bait" by telling him to knock on his front door so his parents would answer.  John Quiñones, a correspondent from US television station ABC News, travelled with the father and son. The father, Adrian Conejo Arias, said they’re happy to be going home. title: At Least Nine Dead In Türkiye Bus Crash | 10 News
description: Authorities say at least nine people have been killed, with a further 26 injured, following a bus crash in Antalya, Türkiye.  The bus was travelling from Tekirdag to Antalya in foggy and rainy conditions, with investigations underway to determine the cause of the crash. title: Iran Leader Warns US Attack Would Spark Regional War | 10 News
description: US President Donald Trump has played down threats of regional war from Iran's supreme leader, saying "of course [he] would say that" and remains hopeful the two nations will make a deal.  "...We have the biggest, most powerful ships in the world over there..." Trump said on Sunday, "...If we don't make a deal, then we'll find out whether or not he was right.”  The United States sent USS Abraham Lincoln and American warships to the Arabian Sea in response to Tehran’s bloody crackdown on nationwide protests. The demonstrations, which began on December 28, 2025, were initially protesting economic issues and low wages, before turning into violent anti-government rallies.  Iranians are calling for an independent inquiry into the number of people killed during recent protests. As many as 30,000 protesters have reportedly been killed, but Iran’s official death toll released by the Martyr’s Foundation is 3,117.
